{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0175Ae251JxZGR2wkN3wnxJN","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've read all five files. Here's the complete content report:\n\n## File Contents Report\n\n### 1. `reward-pool-fund.ts` (lines 1-127)\n**Pattern Summary:**\n- Handler factory pattern: `createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: RewardPoolFundDeps)` returns async function\n- DB helpers for config reading (`readRewardConfig`) and pool mutations (`insertPoolFunding`, `incrementRewardPool`)\n- Idempotency via `ON CONFLICT (round_id) DO NOTHING` on unique constraint\n- Transaction pattern: wraps mutations in `db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {...})`\n- Returns `boolean` from insert to check idempotency\n- Payload shape: `{ roundId: string, feeLamports: string }`\n- Logger usage for info/warn/debug throughout\n\n### 2. `points-grant.ts` (lines 1-180)\n**Pattern Summary:**\n- Handler factory: `createPointsGrantHandler(deps: PointsGrantDeps)` with `db` and `getSolPrice` dependency\n- DB helpers: `insertPointGrant`, `upsertPlayerPoints`, `getActiveDogpileMultiplier`\n- Idempotency via `ON CONFLICT (user_id, source_type, source_id) DO NOTHING`\n- Two grant flows: \"wager\" (calculates from lamports→USD→points) and pre-calculated (crate_points, challenge_completed, bonus_completed)\n- Upsert pattern: `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE SET` to create or increment\n- Payload shape: `{ userId, wallet, sourceType, sourceId, amountLamports?: string, amount?: string, metadata?: object, settledAt?: string }`\n- Same transaction pattern with idempotency guards\n\n### 3. `index.ts` (lines 1-307)\n**Handler Registration (lines 208-226):**\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REWARD_POOL_FUND,\n  createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db }),\n);\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT,\n  createPointsGrantHandler({\n    db,\n    getSolPrice: async () => {\n      const result = await fetchSolPrice();\n      return result?.price ?? null;\n    },\n  }),\n);\n```\n- Handlers registered **before** `createEventWorker` is started (line 229)\n- Import pattern: `import { createEventWorker, registerHandler, EventTypes } from \"./queue/index.js\"`\n\n### 4. `event-types.ts` (lines 1-20)\n**Event Type Definitions:**\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n- **Note:** `CRATE_DROP` and `CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT` are already defined but not yet registered with handlers\n\n### 5. `challenge-adapters.ts` (lines 1-152)\n**Types & Quest Eligibility (lines 18-76):**\n```typescript\nexport interface GameSettledPlayer {\n  userId: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  amountLamports: string;\n  isWinner: boolean | null; // null = refund\n  payoutLamports: string;\n  isCreator: boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface GameSettledPayload {\n  roundId: string;\n  roundPda: string;\n  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\";\n  players: GameSettledPlayer[];\n  feeLamports: string;\n  settledAt: string;\n}\n\nexport function questEligible(player: GameSettledPlayer): boolean {\n  return player.isWinner !== null;\n}\n```\n\n**Adapter Registry (lines 134-150):**\n- Pure functions: `(event: GameSettledPayload, player: GameSettledPlayer, assignment: ChallengeAssignment) => AdapterResult`\n- Returns `{ shouldProgress: boolean, progressDelta: number }`\n- Built-in adapters: `game_completed`, `game_won`, `lobby_filled`\n- Unknown actions log warning and return no-op\n\n---\n\n## Key Implementation Patterns for CRATE_DROP Handler\n\n1. **Factory Function Signature:**\n   ```typescript\n   export function createCrateDropHandler(deps: CrateDropDeps) {\n     const { db } = deps;\n     return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => { ... }\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **DB Helper Pattern:** Extract to functions above handler, use `db.rawSql` for typed queries, return `boolean` from inserts for idempotency checks\n\n3. **Idempotency:** Use `ON CONFLICT (unique_constraint) DO NOTHING RETURNING id`, check `rows.length > 0`\n\n4. **Transaction Wrapper:** `await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => { ... })`\n\n5. **Registration in index.ts:** Add after line 226:\n   ```typescript\n   registerHandler(\n     EventTypes.CRATE_DROP,\n     createCrateDropHandler({ db }),\n   );\n   ```\n\n6. **Payload Validation:** Extract typed fields from payload, throw on missing required fields\n\n7. **Idempotency Guard:** Only proceed if insert succeeded (guards duplicate processing in event queue retries)"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76dd357f-8d88-4f6f-a9bf-260ee83a7c97","uuid":"4f7febd5-75d1-4c36-9ec2-6d379f71d2e2","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:02:03.001Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing reward handler patterns in the backend to implement a new CRATE_DROP handler. Please read these files and report their full contents:\n\n1. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.ts` - existing handler pattern\n2. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/points-grant.ts` - existing handler pattern\n3. `backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` - handler registration\n4. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts` - event types\n5. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts` - quest_eligible and types\n\nReport the FULL content of each file, especially function signatures, DB helper patterns, emitEvent usage, and how handlers are register