{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012BdyNTfHwavXotaDFHedBb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear understanding of everything I need. Let me implement the `CRATE_DROP` handler. Here's what I need to do:\n\n1. Create `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts` with:\n   - `lockAndReadRewardPool(db)` - SELECT ... FOR UPDATE on singleton\n   - `decrementRewardPool(db, payoutLamports)` - atomically decrement balance + increment lifetime_paid\n   - `insertCrateDrop(db, userId, triggerType, triggerId, crateType, contentsAmount)` - with UNIQUE(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id) idempotency\n   \n2. The handler will load the drop rates and pool configuration, then branch based on the roll: for SOL drops, lock the pool, calculate the payout as a percentage of the balance, skip if below the minimum threshold, decrement the pool and emit a payout event; for points drops, generate a random amount within the configured range and emit a grant event; or return early if the roll misses entirely.\n\n3. Register the handler in `index.ts`\n\n4. Now I need to write integration tests and make sure to add `crate_drops` to the TRUNCATE list in the test setup so the table gets cleared between runs.\n\n5. Let me review the FR-5 spec to understand the exact drop mechanics.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1252,"cache_read_input_tokens":58236,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1252},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76dd357f-8d88-4f6f-a9bf-260ee83a7c97","uuid":"50eb1788-c57b-44ca-a1f7-de3b3e32a9a4"}
