{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X8fCnHpVczeCTBZpKjF8uL","type":"tool_result","content":"377\t\n378\t---\n379\t\n380\t### FR-5: Loot Crate Drops\n381\t\n382\tAfter each settled game, each eligible player has a random chance of receiving a loot crate. Two types: points crate (free) and SOL crate (pool-funded by the accounting-only reward pool).\n383\t\n384\t**Drop logic (per player per settled game):**\n385\t```\n386\troll = random()\n387\tif roll < sol_crate_drop_rate AND pool can fund:\n388\t    drop SOL crate (payout = floor(pool.balance * sol_crate_pool_pct))\n389\telif roll < sol_crate_drop_rate + points_crate_drop_rate:\n390\t    drop points crate (amount = random in [points_crate_min, points_crate_max])\n391\telse:\n392\t    no drop\n393\t```\n394\t\n395\tSOL crate is checked first (higher value, lower probability). If pool can't fund it, the roll is wasted (no fallback to points crate — keeps the economics clean).\n396\t\n397\tCrate drops are recorded in `crate_drops` table by a dedicated `crate.drop` handler. SOL crate grants are processed via a new event (`crate.sol_payout`) through the async queue, following the same pattern as `referral.claim_requested` — the handler sends SOL from the treasury-managed payout wallet to the player's wallet.\n398\t\n399\tPoints crate grants do not mutate balances inline. The `crate.drop` handler records the crate, then emits `points.grant` with `source_type = 'crate_points'`.\n400\t\n401\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n402\t- [ ] Eligible settled-game processing emits one `crate.drop` event per eligible player after a `game.settled` event\n403\t- [ ] Drop rates read from `reward_config` (`sol_crate_drop_rate`, `points_crate_drop_rate`)\n404\t- [ ] SOL crate: `reward_pool` row locked (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`), balance checked, payout calculated, pool decremented, `crate_drops` row created — all in one transaction\n405\t- [ ] SOL crate payout emits `crate.sol_payout` event for async SOL transfer\n406\t- [ ] SOL crate suppressed when pool can't fund `sol_crate_min_value`\n407\t- [ ] Points crate: random amount in configured range, `crate_drops` row created, `points.grant` emitted with `source_type = 'crate_points'`\n408\t- [ ] `crate_drops` records trigger_type, trigger_id (round_id), crate_type, contents_amount\n409\t- [ ] No crate drop for games that fail `quest_eligible()` check (FR-10)\n410\t- [ ] Crate drop is idempotent per `(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id)` and enforced with a DB UNIQUE constraint\n411\t\n412\t---\n413\t\n414\t### FR-6: Dogpile Scheduled Events\n415\t\n416\tTime-windowed events (e.g., daily 8-9 PM UTC) that boost the points multiplier for all players. Dogpile creates urgency and concentrates lobby activity.\n417\t\n418\t**Mechanics:**\n419\t- Operator creates a `dogpile_events` row with `starts_at`, `ends_at`, `multiplier` (default 2.0)\n420\t- A scheduler (cron job or worker) transitions events from `scheduled` -> `active` at `starts_at` and `active` -> `ended` at `ends_at`\n421\t- The points calculation (FR-3) checks for an active Dogpile event and applies the multiplier\n422\t- Dogpile can optionally be linked to a campaign with ephemeral challenges (future — not M1)\n423\t\n424\t**Recurring Dogpile:** Operator can schedule repeating events via admin API (creates multiple `dogpile_events` rows). The scheduler pattern is simple: one row per occurrence, no RRULE complexity.\n425\t\n426\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n427\t- [ ] `dogpile_events` table supports scheduling events with start/end times and multiplier\n428\t- [ ] Worker or cron transitions event status: scheduled -> active -> ended at the correct times\n429\t- [ ] Points calculation in FR-3 reads active Dogpile event and applies multiplier\n430\t- [ ] Active Dogpile check is a simple query: `SELECT multiplier FROM dogpile_events WHERE status = 'active' AND now() BETWEEN starts_at AND ends_at LIMIT 1`\n431\t- [ ] Multiple Dogpile events cannot overlap; enforce via admin validation in M1 (DB exclusion constraint not required)\n432\t- [ ] Dogpile events can be cancelled (status -> cancelled) before or during the window\n433\t- [ ] `dogpile_active` and `dogpile_multiplier` are computed in handler context for analytics; they are not required fields on the `game.settled` payload\n434\t\n435\t---\n436\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76dd357f-8d88-4f6f-a9bf-260ee83a7c97","uuid":"d8da86eb-ad89-4349-9e3d-9bed7ce5fa51","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:04:39.054Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/400-challenge-engine/spec.md","content":"\n---\n\n### FR-5: Loot Crate Drops\n\nAfter each settled game, each eligible player has a random chance of receiving a loot crate. Two types: points crate (free) and SOL crate (pool-funded by the accounting-only reward pool).\n\n**Drop logic (per player per settled game):**\n```\nroll = random()\nif roll < sol_crate_drop_rate AND pool can fund:\n    drop SOL crate (payout = floor(pool.balance * sol_crate_pool_pct))\nelif roll < sol_crate_drop_rate + points_crate_drop_rate:\n    drop points crate (amount = random in [points_crate_min, points_crate_max])\nelse:\n    no drop\n```\n\nSOL crate is checked first (higher value, lower probability). If pool can't fund it, the roll is wasted (no fallback to points crate — keeps the economics clean).\n\nCrate drops are recorded in `crate_drops` table by a dedicated `crate.drop` handler. SOL crate grants are processed via a new event (`crate.sol_payout`) through the async queue, following the same pattern as `referral.claim_requested` — the handler sends SOL from the treasury-managed payout wallet to the player's wallet.\n\nPoints crate grants do not mutate balances inline. The `crate.drop` handler records the crate, then emits `points.grant` with `source_type = 'crate_points'`.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Eligible settled-game processing emits one `crate.drop` event per eligible player after a `game.settled` event\n- [ ] Drop rates read from `reward_config` (`sol_crate_drop_rate`, `points_crate_drop_rate`)\n- [ ] SOL crate: `reward_pool` row locked (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`), balance checked, payout calculated, pool decremented, `crate_drops` row created — all in one transaction\n- [ ] SOL crate payout emits `crate.sol_payout` event for async SOL transfer\n- [ ] SOL crate suppressed when pool can't fund `sol_crate_min_value`\n- [ ] Points crate: random amount in configured range, `crate_drops` row created, `points.grant` emitted with `source_type = 'crate_points'`\n- [ ] `crate_drops` records trigger_type, trigger_id (round_id), crate_type, contents_amount\n- [ ] No crate drop for games that fail `quest_eligible()` check (FR-10)\n- [ ] Crate drop is idempotent per `(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id)` and enforced with a DB UNIQUE constraint\n\n---\n\n### FR-6: Dogpile Scheduled Events\n\nTime-windowed events (e.g., daily 8-9 PM UTC) that boost the points multiplier for all players. Dogpile creates urgency and concentrates lobby activity.\n\n**Mechanics:**\n- Operator creates a `dogpile_events` row with `starts_at`, `ends_at`, `multiplier` (default 2.0)\n- A scheduler (cron job or worker) transitions events from `scheduled` -> `active` at `starts_at` and `active` -> `ended` at `ends_at`\n- The points calculation (FR-3) checks for an active Dogpile event and applies the multiplier\n- Dogpile can optionally be linked to a campaign with ephemeral challenges (future — not M1)\n\n**Recurring Dogpile:** Operator can schedule repeating events via admin API (creates multiple `dogpile_events` rows). The scheduler pattern is simple: one row per occurrence, no RRULE complexity.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `dogpile_events` table supports scheduling events with start/end times and multiplier\n- [ ] Worker or cron transitions event status: scheduled -> active -> ended at the correct times\n- [ ] Points calculation in FR-3 reads active Dogpile event and applies multiplier\n- [ ] Active Dogpile check is a simple query: `SELECT multiplier FROM dogpile_events WHERE status = 'active' AND now() BETWEEN starts_at AND ends_at LIMIT 1`\n- [ ] Multiple Dogpile events cannot overlap; enforce via admin validation in M1 (DB exclusion constraint not required)\n- [ ] Dogpile events can be cancelled (status -> cancelled) before or during the window\n- [ ] `dogpile_active` and `dogpile_multiplier` are computed in handler context for analytics; they are not required fields on the `game.settled` payload\n\n---\n","numLines":60,"startLine":377,"totalLines":926}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NTJGTwK3H5mGFuvf8sqiiU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have everything I need. Let me implement the `CRATE_DROP` handler."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1768,"cache_read_input_tokens":59488,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1768},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76dd357f-8d88-4f6f-a9bf-260ee83a7c97","uuid":"5b54e677-9e57-412b-b290-75e28138689d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NTJGTwK3H5mGFuvf8sqiiU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Fb4N9jmVXaQe54bxqvRkao","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts","content":"/**\n * CRATE_DROP handler — rolls for a loot crate drop after a settled game.\n *\n * Drop logic per player per settled game:\n *   roll = random()\n *   if roll < sol_crate_drop_rate AND pool can fund:  → SOL crate\n *   elif roll < sol_crate_drop_rate + points_crate_drop_rate:  → Points crate\n *   else: no drop\n *\n * SOL crate is checked first (higher value, lower probability). If pool can't\n * fund it, the roll is wasted (no fallback to points crate).\n *\n * Idempotent via UNIQUE(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id) on crate_drops.\n */\n\nimport type { Db } from \"../../db.js\";\nimport { logger } from \"../../logger.js\";\nimport { readRewardConfig } from \"./reward-pool-fund.js\";\nimport { emitEvent } from \"../emit-event.js\";\nimport { EventTypes } from \"../event-types.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// DB helpers\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport interface RewardPoolRow {\n  balance_lamports: string;\n  lifetime_paid: string;\n}\n\n/**\n * Lock the reward_pool singleton row for update and return its current state.\n * Must be called within a transaction.\n */\nexport async function lockAndReadRewardPool(\n  db: Db,\n): Promise<RewardPoolRow> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<RewardPoolRow[]>`\n    SELECT balance_lamports, lifetime_paid\n    FROM reward_pool\n    WHERE id = 1\n    FOR UPDATE\n  `;\n  if (rows.length === 0) {\n    throw new Error(\"crate.drop: reward_pool singleton row missing\");\n  }\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\n/**\n * Atomically decrement reward_pool.balance_lamports and increment lifetime_paid.\n * Must be called within a transaction after locking the row.\n */\nexport async function decrementRewardPool(\n  db: Db,\n  payoutLamports: bigint,\n): Promise<void> {\n  await db.rawSql`\n    UPDATE reward_pool\n    SET balance_lamports = balance_lamports - ${payoutLamports},\n        lifetime_paid    = lifetime_paid + ${payoutLamports},\n        updated_at       = now()\n    WHERE id = 1\n  `;\n}\n\n/**\n * Insert a crate drop record. Returns false if a row for this\n * (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id) already exists (idempotency guard).\n */\nexport async function insertCrateDrop(\n  db: Db,\n  userId: string,\n  triggerType: string,\n  triggerId: string,\n  crateType: string,\n  contentsAmount: string,\n): Promise<boolean> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO crate_drops (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id, crate_type, contents_amount)\n    VALUES (${userId}, ${triggerType}, ${triggerId}, ${crateType}, ${contentsAmount})\n    ON CONFLICT (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id) DO NOTHING\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n  return rows.length > 0;\n}\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Handler factory\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport interface CrateDropDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  /** Injectable RNG for deterministic testing. Returns a number in [0, 1). */\n  rollRng?: () => number;\n}\n\nexport function createCrateDropHandler(deps: CrateDropDeps) {\n  const { db, rollRng = Math.random } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const userId = payload.userId as string;\n    const wallet = payload.wallet as string;\n    const triggerType = payload.triggerType as string;\n    const triggerId = payload.triggerId as string;\n\n    if (!userId || !wallet || !triggerType || !triggerId) {\n      throw new Error(\n        \"crate.drop: malformed payload — missing userId, wallet, triggerType, or triggerId\",\n      );\n    }\n\n    // Read all config values upfront (outside transaction to minimise lock time)\n    const [\n      solDropRateStr,\n      pointsDropRateStr,\n      solPoolPctStr,\n      solMinValueStr,\n      pointsCrateMinStr,\n      pointsCrateMaxStr,\n    ] = await Promise.all([\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"sol_crate_drop_rate\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"points_crate_drop_rate\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"sol_crate_pool_pct\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"sol_crate_min_value\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"points_crate_min\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"points_crate_max\"),\n    ]);\n\n    const solDropRate = parseFloat(solDropRateStr ?? \"0\");\n    const pointsDropRate = parseFloat(pointsDropRateStr ?? \"0\");\n    const solPoolPct = parseFloat(solPoolPctStr ?? \"0\");\n    const solMinValue = BigInt(solMinValueStr ?? \"0\");\n    const pointsCrateMin = parseInt(pointsCrateMinStr ?? \"0\", 10);\n    const pointsCrateMax = parseInt(pointsCrateMaxStr ?? \"0\", 10);\n\n    // Roll RNG\n    const roll = rollRng();\n\n    if (roll < solDropRate) {\n      // --- SOL crate path ---\n      await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n        // Lock pool row\n        const pool = await lockAndReadRewardPool(txDb);\n        const poolBalance = BigInt(pool.balance_lamports);\n\n        // Calculate payout: floor(balance * sol_crate_pool_pct)\n        const payoutLamports = BigInt(\n          Math.floor(Number(poolBalance) * solPoolPct),\n        );\n\n        // Suppress if payout < min_value\n        if (payoutLamports < solMinValue) {\n          logger.info(\"crate.drop: SOL crate suppressed — pool below min\", {\n            userId,\n            triggerId,\n            poolBalance: poolBalance.toString(),\n            payoutLamports: payoutLamports.toString(),\n            solMinValue: solMinValue.toString(),\n          });\n          return;\n        }\n\n        // Insert crate record (idempotency guard)\n        const inserted = await insertCrateDrop(\n          txDb,\n          userId,\n          triggerType,\n          triggerId,\n          \"sol\",\n          payoutLamports.toString(),\n        );\n        if (!inserted) {\n          logger.info(\"crate.drop: duplicate crate, skipping\", {\n            userId,\n            triggerType,\n            triggerId,\n          });\n          return;\n        }\n\n        // Decrement pool\n        await decrementRewardPool(txDb, payoutLamports);\n\n        // Emit CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT for async SOL transfer\n        await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT, {\n          userId,\n          wallet,\n          payoutLamports: payoutLamports.toString(),\n          triggerId,\n        });\n\n        logger.info(\"crate.drop: SOL crate dropped\", {\n          userId,\n          triggerId,\n          payoutLamports: payoutLamports.toString(),\n        });\n      });\n    } else if (roll < solDropRate + pointsDropRate) {\n      // --- Points crate path ---\n      const range = pointsCrateMax - pointsCrateMin;\n      const pointsAmount =\n        range > 0\n          ? pointsCrateMin + Math.floor(rollRng() * (range + 1))\n          : pointsCrateMin;\n\n      await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n        // Insert crate record (idempotency guard)\n        const inserted = await insertCrateDrop(\n          txDb,\n          userId,\n          triggerType,\n          triggerId,\n          \"points\",\n          pointsAmount.toString(),\n        );\n        if (!inserted) {\n          logger.info(\"crate.drop: duplicate crate, skipping\", {\n            userId,\n            triggerType,\n            triggerId,\n          });\n          return;\n        }\n\n        // Emit POINTS_GRANT with source_type='crate_points'\n        await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT, {\n          userId,\n          wallet,\n          sourceType: \"crate_points\",\n          sourceId: `crate-${triggerId}`,\n          amount: pointsAmount.toString(),\n        });\n\n        logger.info(\"crate.drop: points crate dropped\", {\n          userId,\n          triggerId,\n          pointsAmount,\n        });\n      });\n    } else {\n      // --- Miss: no drop ---\n      logger.debug(\"crate.drop: no drop\", { userId, triggerId, roll });\n    }\n  };\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1768,"cache_read_input_tokens":59488,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1768},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76dd357f-8d88-4f6f-a9bf-260ee83a7c97","uuid":"9daa6d91-4b7a-4047-8ac3-34a1c604af05"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fb4N9jmVXaQe54bxqvRkao","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76dd357f-8d88-4f6f-a9bf-260ee83a7c97","uuid":"89a94db6-7b65-46d5-8f60-958efa21a934","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:05:08.417Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts","content":"/**\n * CRATE_DROP handler — rolls for a loot crate drop after a settled game.\n *\n * Drop logic per player per settled game:\n *   roll = random()\n *   if roll < sol_crate_drop_rate AND pool can fund:  → SOL crate\n *   elif roll < sol_crate_drop_rate + points_crate_drop_rate:  → Points crate\n *   else: no drop\n *\n * SOL crate is checked first (higher value, lower probability). If pool can't\n * fund it, the roll is wasted (no fallback to points crate).\n *\n * Idempotent via UNIQUE(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id) on crate_drops.\n */\n\nimport type { Db } from \"../../db.js\";\nimport { logger } from \"../../logger.js\";\nimport { readRewardConfig } from \"./reward-pool-fund.js\";\nimport { emitEvent } from \"../emit-event.js\";\nimport { EventTypes } from \"../event-types.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// DB helpers\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport interface RewardPoolRow {\n  balance_lamports: string;\n  lifetime_paid: string;\n}\n\n/**\n * Lock the reward_pool singleton row for update and return its current state.\n * Must be called within a transaction.\n */\nexport async function lockAndReadRewardPool(\n  db: Db,\n): Promise<RewardPoolRow> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<RewardPoolRow[]>`\n    SELECT balance_lamports, lifetime_paid\n    FROM reward_pool\n    WHERE id = 1\n    FOR UPDATE\n  `;\n  if (rows.length === 0) {\n    throw new Error(\"crate.drop: reward_pool singleton row missing\");\n  }\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\n/**\n * Atomically decrement reward_pool.balance_lamports and increment lifetime_paid.\n * Must be called within a transaction after locking the row.\n */\nexport async function decrementRewardPool(\n  db: Db,\n  payoutLamports: bigint,\n): Promise<void> {\n  await db.rawSql`\n    UPDATE reward_pool\n    SET balance_lamports = balance_lamports - ${payoutLamports},\n        lifetime_paid    = lifetime_paid + ${payoutLamports},\n        updated_at       = now()\n    WHERE id = 1\n  `;\n}\n\n/**\n * Insert a crate drop record. Returns false if a row for this\n * (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id) already exists (idempotency guard).\n */\nexport async function insertCrateDrop(\n  db: Db,\n  userId: string,\n  triggerType: string,\n  triggerId: string,\n  crateType: string,\n  contentsAmount: string,\n): Promise<boolean> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO crate_drops (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id, crate_type, contents_amount)\n    VALUES (${userId}, ${triggerType}, ${triggerId}, ${crateType}, ${contentsAmount})\n    ON CONFLICT (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id) DO NOTHING\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n  return rows.length > 0;\n}\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Handler factory\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport interface CrateDropDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  /** Injectable RNG for deterministic testing. Returns a number in [0, 1). */\n  rollRng?: () => number;\n}\n\nexport function createCrateDropHandler(deps: CrateDropDeps) {\n  const { db, rollRng = Math.random } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const userId = payload.userId as string;\n    const wallet = payload.wallet as string;\n    const triggerType = payload.triggerType as string;\n    const triggerId = payload.triggerId as string;\n\n    if (!userId || !wallet || !triggerType || !triggerId) {\n      throw new Error(\n        \"crate.drop: malformed payload — missing userId, wallet, triggerType, or triggerId\",\n      );\n    }\n\n    // Read all config values upfront (outside transaction to minimise lock time)\n    const [\n      solDropRateStr,\n      pointsDropRateStr,\n      solPoolPctStr,\n      solMinValueStr,\n      pointsCrateMinStr,\n      pointsCrateMaxStr,\n    ] = await Promise.all([\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"sol_crate_drop_rate\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"points_crate_drop_rate\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"sol_crate_pool_pct\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"sol_crate_min_value\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"points_crate_min\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"points_crate_max\"),\n    ]);\n\n    const solDropRate = parseFloat(solDropRateStr ?? \"0\");\n    const pointsDropRate = parseFloat(pointsDropRateStr ?? \"0\");\n    const solPoolPct = parseFloat(solPoolPctStr ?? \"0\");\n    const solMinValue = BigInt(solMinValueStr ?? \"0\");\n    const pointsCrateMin = parseInt(pointsCrateMinStr ?? \"0\", 10);\n    const pointsCrateMax = parseInt(pointsCrateMaxStr ?? \"0\", 10);\n\n    // Roll RNG\n    const roll = rollRng();\n\n    if (roll < solDropRate) {\n      // --- SOL crate path ---\n      await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n        // Lock pool row\n        const pool = await lockAndReadRewardPool(txDb);\n        const poolBalance = BigInt(pool.balance_lamports);\n\n        // Calculate payout: floor(balance * sol_crate_pool_pct)\n        const payoutLamports = BigInt(\n          Math.floor(Number(poolBalance) * solPoolPct),\n        );\n\n        // Suppress if payout < min_value\n        if (payoutLamports < solMinValue) {\n          logger.info(\"crate.drop: SOL crate suppressed — pool below min\", {\n            userId,\n            triggerId,\n            poolBalance: poolBalance.toString(),\n            payoutLamports: payoutLamports.toString(),\n            solMinValue: solMinValue.toString(),\n          });\n          return;\n        }\n\n        // Insert crate record (idempotency guard)\n        const inserted = await insertCrateDrop(\n          txDb,\n          userId,\n          triggerType,\n          triggerId,\n          \"sol\",\n          payoutLamports.toString(),\n        );\n        if (!inserted) {\n          logger.info(\"crate.drop: duplicate crate, skipping\", {\n            userId,\n            triggerType,\n            triggerId,\n          });\n          return;\n        }\n\n        // Decrement pool\n        await decrementRewardPool(txDb, payoutLamports);\n\n        // Emit CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT for async SOL transfer\n        await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT, {\n          userId,\n          wallet,\n          payoutLamports: payoutLamports.toString(),\n          triggerId,\n        });\n\n        logger.info(\"crate.drop: SOL crate dropped\", {\n          userId,\n          triggerId,\n          payoutLamports: payoutLamports.toString(),\n        });\n      });\n    } else if (roll < solDropRate + pointsDropRate) {\n      // --- Points crate path ---\n      const range = pointsCrateMax - pointsCrateMin;\n      const pointsAmount =\n        range > 0\n          ? pointsCrateMin + Math.floor(rollRng() * (range + 1))\n          : pointsCrateMin;\n\n      await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n        // Insert crate record (idempotency guard)\n        const inserted = await insertCrateDrop(\n          txDb,\n          userId,\n          triggerType,\n          triggerId,\n          \"points\",\n          pointsAmount.toString(),\n        );\n        if (!inserted) {\n          logger.info(\"crate.drop: duplicate crate, skipping\", {\n            userId,\n            triggerType,\n            triggerId,\n          });\n          return;\n        }\n\n        // Emit POINTS_GRANT with source_type='crate_points'\n        await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT, {\n          userId,\n          wallet,\n          sourceType: \"crate_points\",\n          sourceId: `crate-${triggerId}`,\n          amount: pointsAmount.toString(),\n        });\n\n        logger.info(\"crate.drop: points crate dropped\", {\n          userId,\n          triggerId,\n          pointsAmount,\n        });\n      });\n    } else {\n      // --- Miss: no drop ---\n      logger.debug(\"crate.drop: no drop\", { userId, triggerId, roll });\n    }\n  };\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
